# Titan MCP Orchestration

When generating UI through Cursor + MCP for this repository, follow this order:

1. Use `@audienseco/titan-react` component first when available in product version.
2. If missing, use React Aria primitives + Titan tokens/foundations as fallback.
3. For icons: use Titan React icons first; if missing, use `lucide-react`.

## Components treated as official in Titan React (current team context)

- Stable: `AudienseEcosystemMenu`, `Button Group`, `Buttons`, `Checkbox`, `Dialog`, `Label`, `NavBar`, `Pagination`, `Pill`, `Radio Buttons`, `Tabs`, `Tooltip`.
- Also treated as official (used in production): `ActionableIcon`, `Avatar`, `Badge`, `Charts`, `Divider`, `Flag`, `GridList`, `Icons`, `Link`, `Loading`, `MatchHighlighter`, `Menu`, `PlatformIcon`, `Popover`, `RefreshSpinner`, `Select`, `Table`, `Toast`, `Toggle`, `Accordion`, `Collapsible`, `Combobox`, `Input`, `TagGroup`, `TextArea`, `TextField`.

## Local fallback ownership notes

- `Navbar`, `Menu`, and `Select` local specs/rules are fallback/reference only.
- `Drawer` remains fallback with React Aria + Titan tokens unless official Titan React support is confirmed in current version.

## Non-collision rule

- Never output two "official" implementations for the same component in one solution.
- If using fallback, mark it as temporary (`snowflake`) and align with integration docs.

